0.2 Test correlations and Summary

########### summary ###############
clinical_sum <- matrix(NA, 14, 14)
alpha <- 0.05
for (i in 1:n_clinical) {
    ## number of clinical virable
    j = c(6:19)[i]
    cliname = base::colnames(clinical_order)[j]
    ## linear regression
    lin_res_isgs = gene_IFNReg(isgs.05.lin, clinical_order[, 
        j], clinical_names[i])
    lin_res_genesbeta = gene_IFNReg(genesbeta.05.lin, clinical_order[, 
        j], clinical_names[i])
    ## save data
    
    write.xlsx(lin_res_isgs$results, paste("~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/sum/isgs_", 
        cliname, ".xlsx", sep = ""), sheetName = paste("ISGs_", 
        cliname, sep = ""))
    
    write.xlsx(lin_res_genesbeta$results, paste("~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/sum/ifnbeta_", 
        cliname, ".xlsx", sep = ""), sheetName = paste("ifnbeta_", 
        cliname, sep = ""))
    # } check basic
    if (lin_res_isgs$size == lin_res_genesbeta$size) {
        print("Good size")
        size = lin_res_isgs$size
    } else stop("sample size wrong")
    if (lin_res_isgs$clinical == lin_res_genesbeta$clinical) {
        print("Good outcome")
        clinical = lin_res_isgs$clinical
    } else stop("clinical parameter wrong")
    ## number of genes
    nisgs = nrow(lin_res_isgs$results)
    ngenesbeta = nrow(lin_res_genesbeta$results)
    ## results
    isgs_lm = data.frame(lin_res_isgs$results)
    genesbeta_lm = data.frame(lin_res_genesbeta$results)
    ## xlim
    xrange = c(range(isgs_lm$Estimate) * 1.3, range(genesbeta_lm$Estimate) * 
        1.3)
    ################## summary table ################### sig prop
    isgs.sig.no = sum(isgs_lm$FDR < 0.05)
    genesbeta.sig.no = sum(genesbeta_lm$FDR < 0.05)
    if ((isgs.sig.no >= 5) & (genesbeta.sig.no >= 5)) {
        prop.test.sig = prop.test(x = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), 
            n = c(nisgs, ngenesbeta), correct = FALSE)
        sig.p = format(prop.test.sig$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = T)
    } else {
        prop.test.sig = prop.test(x = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), 
            n = c(nisgs, ngenesbeta), correct = TRUE)
        sig.p = format(prop.test.sig$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = T)
    }
    ########### volcano plots ################
    if (min(isgs_lm$FDR) < 0.05) {
        rownames(isgs_lm) <- isgs_lm$names
        p_cutoff <- isgs_lm$p.value[min(which(isgs_lm$FDR >= 
            0.05))]
        p1 <- ggplot(isgs_lm, aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value))) + 
            geom_point(colour = "gray65") + geom_point(data = subset(isgs_lm, 
            FDR < 0.05 & Estimate > 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "black") + geom_point(data = subset(isgs_lm, 
            FDR < 0.05 & Estimate < 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "gray35") + geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(p_cutoff), 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0, 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + labs(x = expression(paste("Slope")), 
            y = expression(paste("-", log[10], " p-value")), 
            caption = paste("Core ISGs: associations with ", 
                clinical, sep = "")) + annotate(geom = "text", 
            x = max(xrange)/1.2, y = -log10(p_cutoff - 0.005), 
            label = "FDR < 0.05", color = "black") + xlim(min(xrange), 
            max(xrange)) + theme_bw()
        
        ggsave(paste("Volcanol_Plot_ISGs_", cliname, sep = ""), 
            width = 6, height = 9, device = "tiff", path = "~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/plots", 
            dpi = 300)
        print(p1)
    } else {
        print("No Sig.")
    }
    
    if (min(genesbeta_lm$FDR) < 0.05) {
        rownames(genesbeta_lm) <- genesbeta_lm$names
        p_cutoff2 <- genesbeta_lm$p.value[min(which(genesbeta_lm$FDR >= 
            0.05))]
        p2 <- ggplot(genesbeta_lm, aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value))) + 
            geom_point(colour = "gray65") + geom_point(data = subset(genesbeta_lm, 
            FDR < 0.05 & Estimate > 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "black") + geom_point(data = subset(genesbeta_lm, 
            FDR < 0.05 & Estimate < 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "gray35") + geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(p_cutoff2), 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0, 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + labs(x = expression(paste("Slope")), 
            y = expression(paste("-", log[10], " p-value")), 
            caption = paste("IFN-Beta Genes: associations with ", 
                clinical, sep = "")) + annotate(geom = "text", 
            x = max(xrange)/1.2, y = -log10(p_cutoff2 - 0.005), 
            label = "FDR < 0.05", color = "black") + xlim(min(xrange), 
            max(xrange)) + theme_bw()
        
        ggsave(paste("Volcanol_Plot_IFNBeta_", cliname, sep = ""), 
            width = 6, height = 9, device = "tiff", path = "~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/plots", 
            dpi = 300)
        print(p2)
    } else {
        print("No Sig.")
    }
    
    ## positive prop
    isgs.pos.no = sum(isgs_lm$Estimate > 0 & isgs_lm$FDR < 0.05)
    genesbeta.pos.no = sum(genesbeta_lm$Estimate > 0 & genesbeta_lm$FDR < 
        0.05)
    if (isgs.sig.no == 0 | genesbeta.sig.no == 0) {
        pos.p = NA
    } else {
        if ((isgs.pos.no >= 5) & (genesbeta.pos.no >= 5)) {
            prop.test.pos = prop.test(x = c(isgs.pos.no, genesbeta.pos.no), 
                n = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), correct = FALSE)
            pos.p = format(prop.test.pos$p.value, digits = 2, 
                scientific = T)
        } else {
            prop.test.pos = prop.test(x = c(isgs.pos.no, genesbeta.pos.no), 
                n = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), correct = TRUE)
            pos.p = format(prop.test.pos$p.value, digits = 2, 
                scientific = T)
        }
    }
    ## If you check prop.test, chisq.test and z-test on your data
    ## then they all give you the same p-value continuity
    ## correction if anyone less than 5 the clinical summary table
    print(clinical)
    clinical_sum[i, ] <- c(clinical, size, nisgs, ngenesbeta, 
        isgs.sig.no, round(isgs.sig.no/nisgs, 2), genesbeta.sig.no, 
        round(genesbeta.sig.no/ngenesbeta, 2), sig.p, isgs.pos.no, 
        round(isgs.pos.no/isgs.sig.no, 2), genesbeta.pos.no, 
        round(genesbeta.pos.no/genesbeta.sig.no, 2), pos.p)
    
    colnames(clinical_sum) <- c("Clinical Parameter", "Sample Size", 
        "ISGs", "IFN-Beta", "No. Sig. ISGs", "ISGs Sig.", "No. Sig. IFN-Betas", 
        "IFNbeta Sig.", "p value", "No. Pos. ISGs", "ISGs Pos. Prop.", 
        "No. Pos. IFN-Betas", "IFNbeta Pos. Prop.", "p value (Pos)")
}

########### summary ###############
clinical_sum <- matrix(NA, 14, 14)
alpha <- 0.1
for (i in 1:n_clinical) {
    ## number of clinical virable
    j = c(6:19)[i]
    cliname = base::colnames(clinical_order)[j]
    ## linear regression
    lin_res_isgs = gene_IFNReg(isgs.05.lin, clinical_order[, 
        j], clinical_names[i])
    lin_res_genesbeta = gene_IFNReg(genesbeta.05.lin, clinical_order[, 
        j], clinical_names[i])
    ## save data
    
    write.xlsx(lin_res_isgs$results, paste("~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/sum/isgs_", 
        cliname, ".xlsx", sep = ""), sheetName = paste("ISGs_", 
        cliname, sep = ""))
    
    write.xlsx(lin_res_genesbeta$results, paste("~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/sum/ifnbeta_", 
        cliname, ".xlsx", sep = ""), sheetName = paste("ifnbeta_", 
        cliname, sep = ""))
    # } check basic
    if (lin_res_isgs$size == lin_res_genesbeta$size) {
        print("Good size")
        size = lin_res_isgs$size
    } else stop("sample size wrong")
    if (lin_res_isgs$clinical == lin_res_genesbeta$clinical) {
        print("Good outcome")
        clinical = lin_res_isgs$clinical
    } else stop("clinical parameter wrong")
    ## number of genes
    nisgs = nrow(lin_res_isgs$results)
    ngenesbeta = nrow(lin_res_genesbeta$results)
    ## results
    isgs_lm = data.frame(lin_res_isgs$results)
    genesbeta_lm = data.frame(lin_res_genesbeta$results)
    ## xlim
    xrange = c(range(isgs_lm$Estimate) * 1.3, range(genesbeta_lm$Estimate) * 
        1.3)
    ################## summary table ################### sig prop
    isgs.sig.no = sum(isgs_lm$FDR < alpha)
    genesbeta.sig.no = sum(genesbeta_lm$FDR < alpha)
    if ((isgs.sig.no >= 5) & (genesbeta.sig.no >= 5)) {
        prop.test.sig = prop.test(x = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), 
            n = c(nisgs, ngenesbeta), correct = FALSE)
        sig.p = format(prop.test.sig$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = T)
    } else {
        prop.test.sig = prop.test(x = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), 
            n = c(nisgs, ngenesbeta), correct = TRUE)
        sig.p = format(prop.test.sig$p.value, digits = 2, scientific = T)
    }
    ########### volcano plots ################
    if (min(isgs_lm$FDR) < alpha) {
        rownames(isgs_lm) <- isgs_lm$names
        p_cutoff <- isgs_lm$p.value[min(which(isgs_lm$FDR >= 
            alpha))]
        p1 <- ggplot(isgs_lm, aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value))) + 
            geom_point(colour = "gray65") + geom_point(data = subset(isgs_lm, 
            FDR < alpha & Estimate > 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "black") + geom_point(data = subset(isgs_lm, 
            FDR < alpha & Estimate < 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "gray35") + geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(p_cutoff), 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0, 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + labs(x = expression(paste("Slope")), 
            y = expression(paste("-", log[10], " p-value")), 
            caption = paste("Core ISGs: associations with ", 
                clinical, sep = "")) + annotate(geom = "text", 
            x = max(xrange)/1.2, y = -log10(p_cutoff - 0.02), 
            label = "FDR < 0.1", color = "black") + xlim(min(xrange), 
            max(xrange)) + theme_bw()
        
        ggsave(paste("Volcanol_Plot_ISGs_01_", cliname, sep = ""), 
            width = 6, height = 9, device = "tiff", path = "~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/plots", 
            dpi = 300)
        print(p1)
    } else {
        print("No Sig.")
    }
    
    if (min(genesbeta_lm$FDR) < alpha) {
        rownames(genesbeta_lm) <- genesbeta_lm$names
        p_cutoff2 <- genesbeta_lm$p.value[min(which(genesbeta_lm$FDR >= 
            alpha))]
        p2 <- ggplot(genesbeta_lm, aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value))) + 
            geom_point(colour = "gray65") + geom_point(data = subset(genesbeta_lm, 
            FDR < alpha & Estimate > 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "black") + geom_point(data = subset(genesbeta_lm, 
            FDR < alpha & Estimate < 0), aes(Estimate, -log10(p.value)), 
            colour = "gray35") + geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(p_cutoff2), 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0, 
            linetype = "dashed", color = "black") + labs(x = expression(paste("Slope")), 
            y = expression(paste("-", log[10], " p-value")), 
            caption = paste("IFN-Beta Genes: associations with ", 
                clinical, sep = "")) + annotate(geom = "text", 
            x = max(xrange)/1.2, y = -log10(p_cutoff2 - 0.02), 
            label = "FDR < 0.1", color = "black") + xlim(min(xrange), 
            max(xrange)) + theme_bw()
        
        ggsave(paste("Volcanol_Plot_IFNBeta_01_", cliname, sep = ""), 
            width = 6, height = 9, device = "tiff", path = "~/Documents/gitlab/Cario_RNASeq_Microbiom_Inte/DataProcessed/interferome/plots", 
            dpi = 300)
        print(p2)
    } else {
        print("No Sig.")
    }
    
    ## positive prop
    isgs.pos.no = sum(isgs_lm$Estimate > 0 & isgs_lm$FDR < alpha)
    genesbeta.pos.no = sum(genesbeta_lm$Estimate > 0 & genesbeta_lm$FDR < 
        alpha)
    if (isgs.sig.no == 0 | genesbeta.sig.no == 0) {
        pos.p = NA
    } else {
        if ((isgs.pos.no >= 5) & (genesbeta.pos.no >= 5)) {
            prop.test.pos = prop.test(x = c(isgs.pos.no, genesbeta.pos.no), 
                n = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), correct = FALSE)
            pos.p = format(prop.test.pos$p.value, digits = 2, 
                scientific = T)
        } else {
            prop.test.pos = prop.test(x = c(isgs.pos.no, genesbeta.pos.no), 
                n = c(isgs.sig.no, genesbeta.sig.no), correct = TRUE)
            pos.p = format(prop.test.pos$p.value, digits = 2, 
                scientific = T)
        }
    }
    ## If you check prop.test, chisq.test and z-test on your data
    ## then they all give you the same p-value continuity
    ## correction if anyone less than 5 the clinical summary table
    print(clinical)
    clinical_sum[i, ] <- c(clinical, size, nisgs, ngenesbeta, 
        isgs.sig.no, round(isgs.sig.no/nisgs, 2), genesbeta.sig.no, 
        round(genesbeta.sig.no/ngenesbeta, 2), sig.p, isgs.pos.no, 
        round(isgs.pos.no/isgs.sig.no, 2), genesbeta.pos.no, 
        round(genesbeta.pos.no/genesbeta.sig.no, 2), pos.p)
    
    colnames(clinical_sum) <- c("Clinical Parameter", "Sample Size", 
        "ISGs", "IFN-Beta", "No. Sig. ISGs", "ISGs Sig.", "No. Sig. IFN-Betas", 
        "IFNbeta Sig.", "p value", "No. Pos. ISGs", "ISGs Pos. Prop.", 
        "No. Pos. IFN-Betas", "IFNbeta Pos. Prop.", "p value (Pos)")
}
